{"lastModified":1761160412671,"uri":"c::18263540498::vessel::4a652800-8a9c-11f0-95f7-198daa9e7e53","yachtType":["Sailing","Catamaran"],"description":"Operating Area: Greece\n\nThe Bali 4.0 is the first model in Catana Group’s revolutionary series of catamarans, designed and launched in 2016. With innovative design and unique features, it combines comfort and functionality, offering a pioneering sailing experience. The catamaran boasts a distinctive fore cockpit, not just a simple net but a comfortable area for relaxation with stunning views. At the aft, there is a flip-down hatch that integrates into the “roof” of the central superstructure, creating a seamless layout that allows excellent circulation and ventilation throughout the vessel.\n\nWhat makes the Bali 4.0 stand out is its ability to blur the boundaries between indoor and outdoor spaces, giving passengers a sense of freedom and openness. The interior can transform into a spacious cockpit, thanks to the lateral and front windows that create the illusion of limitless space. Access to the sea is easy and direct, making it ideal for those who want an immersive connection with the maritime environment.\n\nThe Bali 4.0 is equipped with four double cabins, each with private heads, along with two skipper cabins, accommodating up to ten passengers comfortably. For added luxury, it also includes a full bimini top, a spacious upper deck and lounge area, and an electric WC. The new wooden details in the interior add a touch of elegance and high-end aesthetics.\n\nIts independence is enhanced by the presence of a generator and a water maker, allowing passengers to enjoy all the comforts of an autonomous journey, complete with air conditioning even while sailing. The Bali 4.0 is the ideal sanctuary for sailing enthusiasts seeking a blend of luxury, innovation, and functionality, offering a unique sailing experience with style and comfort.","blueprint":{"name":"BLUE DREAM II","images":["/media/media::image::a::vessel::4a